div4.p:
While the primary role of the MathML content element set is to directly encode the mathematical structure of expressions independent of the notation used to present the objects, rendering issues cannot be ignored. Each content element has a default rendering, given in
, and several mechanisms (including 
) are provided for associating a particular rendering with an object.

div5.p:
The factorial element is a 
unary arithmetic operator (see 
).

The divide element is a 
binary arithmetic operator (see 
).

The root element is an 
operator taking qualifiers (see 
).

The divergence element is a 
unary calculus operator (see 
).
